description: Inclusionary Development Units/BPDA Income-Restricted South Boston 1-bedroom/1-bath condo on the 2nd floor. Renovated in 2023, condo includes off-site, professionally-managed elevator building, refinished hardwood floors, fresh paint, in-unit washer/dryer, & Central AC. Sale subject to BPDA approval of buyer(s) eligibility. 1-member household income must be between $114,300-$137,160 & 2-member household income must be between $130,600-$156,720. Please ask for income limits for larger households. Buyer(s) must have under $100,000 in liquid assets (excluding most retirement & education savings) & obtain mortgage financing. Buyer(s) must use this condo as their primary residence. BPDA requires buyers to contribute at least 1.5% of purchase price from their own savings. Buyer(s) must complete affidavit of eligibility and be approved by BPDA/MOH after offer acceptance. Showing Instructions: Only showings at Open Houses on Friday, Nov. 1st, 4:30-6:00pm & Saturday, Nov. 2nd, 11:00am-12:30pm.
